label.value: abnormal centroacinar cell of Langerhans morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of cells that line the pancreatic ducts that secrete mucins and an aqueous bicarbonate solution under stimulation by the hormone secretin
any functional anomaly of the epithelial layer of the luminal surfaces of the mammary gland
increase in the expansion rate of the cells of the mammary gland epithelium by cell division
decrease in the expansion rate of the cells of the mammary gland epithelium by cell division

the presence of unusually thin or flattened red blood cells that when stained show a dark center and a peripheral ring of hemoglobin, separated by a pale unstained ring containing less hemoglobin, resulting in a bull's-eye appearance and resembling a 3D sombrero when viewed under EM; seen in certain anemias, thalassemias, hemoglobinopathies, obstructive jaundice, and the post-splenectomy state
presence of teardrop-shaped red blood cells
presence of erythrocytes characterized by multiple spiny (thorn-like) cytoplasmic projections

abnormal presence of basophilic nuclear remnants of condensed DNA (1 to 2 um in diameter) in circulating erythrocytes, typically seen in severe hemolytic anemias or after splenectomy; these inclusions are normally removed by the spleen but will persist in individuals with functional hyposplenia or asplenia
coat does not have the usual smooth appearance
greater decrease in body weight over time when compared to the average decrease in weight in response to dietary modification, fasting or caloric restriction, infection or xenobiotic treatment
smaller decrease in body weight over time when compared to the average decrease in weight in response to dietary modification, fasting or caloric restriction, infection or xenobiotic treatment
smaller increase in body weight over time when compared to the average increase in weight on the same diet, with equal energy (calorie) intake

label.value: abnormal CD4-positive helper T cell morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that cooperates with other lymphocytes via direct contact or cytokine release to initiate a variety of immune functions

label.value: abnormal T follicular helper cell morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of a CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cell located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses high levels of BCL-6, ICOS and PD1 and stimulate follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production

label.value: abnormal T follicular helper cell number

value.value: anomaly in the number of the CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cells located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses high levels of BCL-6, ICOS and PD1 and stimulate follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production

label.value: increased T follicular helper cell number

value.value: greater number of the CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cells located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses high levels of BCL-6, ICOS and PD1 and stimulate follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production

label.value: decreased T follicular helper cell number

value.value: reduced number of the CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cells located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses high levels of BCL-6, ICOS and PD1 and stimulate follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production

label.value: abnormal T follicular helper cell differentiation

value.value: atypical production of or inability to produce the CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cells located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses high levels of BCL-6, ICOS and PD1 and stimulate follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production

label.value: abnormal T follicular helper cell physiology

value.value: any functional anomaly of a CD4-positive, CXCR5-positive, CCR7-negative alpha-beta T cell located in follicles of secondary lymph nodes that expresses high levels of BCL-6, ICOS and PD1 and stimulate follicular B cells to undergo class-switching and antibody production
any structural anomaly of the cells that produce pigment in the retina
any structural anomaly of the cells that produce pigment in the choroid
any structural anomaly of the pigment particles in the retina
any structural anomaly of the pigment particles in the choroid
absence of the network of vessels which carries lymph around the body
any structural anomaly of the thin layer of flat cells that line the lymphatic vessels and form a barrier between circulating lymph in the lumen and the rest of the vessel wall

label.value: abnormal lymphatic vessel smooth muscle morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the nonstriated, involuntary muscle tissue that encompasses the lymphatic vessels

label.value: abnormal lymphatic vessel endothelial cell morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the cells that line the lymphatic vessels

label.value: decreased lymphatic vessel endothelial cell number

value.value: reduced number of the cells that line the lymphatic vessels
absence of the cells that line the lymphatic vessels
increased size of the network of vessels which carries lymph around the body
focal hair loss on the dorsal area of a rodent resulting in dorsal skin visible in a patch where hair loss occurs
focal hair loss on the ventral area of a rodent resulting in ventral skin visible in a patch where hair loss occurs
change in the timing or the number of astrocytes undergoing programmed cell death
change in the timing or the number of oligodendrocytes undergoing programmed cell death
absence of melanin and melanosomes in the epidermis, and accumulation of melanin and melanosome in melanophages in the upper dermis

any structural anomaly of the terminal repetitive DNA section of a chromosome which is involved in chromosomal replication and senescence, and which protects the end of the chromosome from deterioration
abnormal protrusion of the mandible relative to the facial skeleton and soft tissues
deviation from the normal levels of any of the class of pro-inflammatory cytokines that attract and activate leukocytes in the circulation

definition.value: The site en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemokine has a good list of chemokines.

value.value: deviation from the normal levels in the blood of any of the non-antibody proteins made by inflammatory leukocytes and some non-leukocytic cells that affect the behavior of other cells
deviation from the normal levels of the series of proteins found in the blood shortly after infection and which participate in the early phases of host defense against infection

deviation from the normal levels of the plasma protein that circulates in increased amounts during inflammation or after tissue damage and binds to phosphocholine expressed on the surface of dead or dying cells, including all types of pneumococci, in order to activate the complement system via the C1Q complex
deviation from the normal levels in the blood of a globulin that is converted into fibrin by the action of thrombin in the presence of ionized calcium to produce coagulation of the blood

label.value: abnormal circulating serum amyloid protein level

value.value: deviation from the normal blood levels of an acute-phase reaction protein that is a precursor to amyloid A protein; it is present in very high levels during acute inflammatory episodes, and is present in low concentrations in normal sera, but is found at higher concentrations in sera of older persons and in patients with amyloidosis

deviation from the normal levels of the serum proteins that act sequentially to allow for the direct killing of microbes, the disposal of immune complexes, and the regulation of other immune processes

label.value: abnormal circulating retinol binding protein level

value.value: anomaly in the blood level of carrier proteins that bind retinol; serum levels are used to detect liver disease, protein-calorie malnutrition and vitamin A deficiencies
any structural anomaly of a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive that produces IL-17
deviation from the normal count of CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive that produces IL-17
increased number of CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive that produces IL-17
reduced number of CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive that produces IL-17
atypical production of or inability to produce the CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive that produces IL-17
